<HEADLINE> OAU To Set up Radio Station </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 6 (Xinhua) --Ministers of information of the 53
member countries of the Organisation of African Unity (OAU) are
due to meet in the Egyptian capital, Cairo, from June 17 to 19 to
discuss information and communication issues affecting the
continent, the OAU spokesman of Ibrahim Dagash said here today.
</P>
<P>
He said, ''Major issues which will dominate debate will be the
program of action for 1997-99 of the Inter-Governmental Council
for Communication in Africa (ICC), privatisation of the Pan
African News Agency (PANA) and the setting up of an OAU radio
broadcasting station.''
</P>
<P>
The OAU, which has PANA as its print media agency, now intends
to establish radio transmission to broadcast programs under the
title of ''Voice of Africa''.
</P>
<P>
He said, ''such a project is very important at the moment
because the OAU is trying to be very relevant and to be known to
the ordinary African.''
</P>
<P>
''The radio, we believe, is still the most far-reaching medium
accessible to the African majority,'' he said.
The radio station is likely to be based in Ethiopia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
