<HEADLINE> Bilharzia Rampant in Swaziland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 6 (Xinhua) -- About 15 percent of children in
Swaziland are suffering bilharzia, Swaziland's Health Ministery
announced today.
</P>
<P>
The parasitic disease, the common sysptom of which is blood in the
urine, is prevalent primaily in the rural Lowveld areas of eastern
Swaziland, said a report reaching here .
</P>
<P>
Unless irredicated, bilharzia could spread across the border to
Mpumalanga of South Africa, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Sibongile Maseko, a senior official in Swaziland's Health Ministry
said that the chances of eliminating the disease were low becasse
medical departments in Swaziland are short of money. 
</P>
</TEXT>
