<HEADLINE> Ukrainian PM to Visit Canada Next Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian Prime Minister Pavlo
Lazarenko will visit Canada from June 12 to 16, Prime Minister
Jean Chretien announced today.
</P>
<P>
"This visit will allow Canada and Ukraine to enhance
cooperation in areas of mutual interest such as Euro-Atlantic
security and greater bilateral trade and investment," Chretien
said in a release.
</P>
<P>
Lazarenko's visit coincides with the second meeting of the
Intergovernmental Economic Commission on June 15 in Calgary.
</P>
<P>
As the centerpiece of the Canada-Ukraine Economic Cooperation
Agreement, the commission encourages business and trade
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Lazarenko will meet with Prime Minister Jean
Chretien here in Ottawa. Then, he will travel to Winnipeg and
Calgary.
</P>
<P>
He will be accompanied by Vice Prime Minister Mykhailo Zubets
and other senior Ukrainian ministers. 
</P>
