<HEADLINE> Italian Generals Reported To Have Committed Human Rights Violations in Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, June 6 (Xinhua)--An islamic court in north
Mogadishu has invited three Italian generals to appear in court
to answer allegations of human rights violations during their
activities as part of the U.N. multi-national forces operation of
UNOSOM.
</P>
<P>
The invited generals are. C.Fiore, Bruno Loi and Gambiero
Rossi who each has been the commander of the Italian contingent
of UNOSOM in separate times.
</P>
<P>
The invitation of the court came after a local organization,
the Somali Intellectuals Society (SIS), has submitted to the
court a complaint against the behaviors of the Italian military
personnel towards the Somali nationals in north Mogadishu,
Jowhar, Balad and Aden Yabal districts of Middle Shabelle Region.
The organization has accused the Italians for carrying out human
rights violations such as killing, rape, torture and propertty
destruction.
</P>
<P>
The intellectuals organization said these violations were
conducted by a brigade from the Italian regular army known as
BIS. The SIS also said that a number of Somalis have died while
many more others are still suffering from the effects of the
human roghts violation committed by the Italian army during their
stay in Somalia in 1993-1994.
</P>
<P>
A local human rights organization, Dr Ismail Jumale Human
Rights Center, has supported the SIS complaint and said they have
all the neccessary evidences to prove the mal-behavior of the
Italians. Hassan Shire Sheikh, one of the two co-chairing persons
of the human rights in north Mogadishu, said photos show somalis
being tortured and others who have been buried from the waist to
the legs and being beaten on the head by two Italian soldiers.
</P>
<P>
The human rights organization has called the Italian govenment
to take the responsibility and conduct an official investigation
on the allegations by taking those reponsible to justice and pay
compensations about the human lives loss, torture and the
destruction of properties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
