<HEADLINE> Low-Cholesterol Eggs Produced in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Greek scientists have produced
low-cholesterol eggs with no change to taste or smell.
</P>
<P>
The eggs, known as Omega Eggs, were reportedly created on an
experimental basis on the premises of the American Farm School by
scientists from the Veterinary Department of Thessaloniki
University in northern Greece, according to the newspaper Athens
News today.
</P>
<P>
The eggs contain very low levels of cholesterol and high
quantities of Omega 3 fatty acid, which help the human body form
chemicals know as prostaglandins, which lower the coagulation of
the blood, thus preventing blood clots.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted Greek scientists as saying that Omega 3
acids lower arterial pressure while relieving the danger of
arthritis, high blood pressure, eczema and even some types of
cancer.
</P>
<P>
They stressed that no genetic engineering or hormone tampering
was involved in making the Omega Eggs, whose high levels of
unsaturated fatty acids were achieved through a special feeding
program for hens at the school. 
</P>
</TEXT>
