<HEADLINE> Exploded Oil Tanker Under Control, Police Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The fire in an oil tanker which exploded
here in the middle of today has been brought under control, the
Nigerian Television Authority reported tonight.
</P>
<P>
A witness told Xinhua over the phone earlier the explosion happened
in a pleasure-boat in the lagoon.
</P>
<P>
Lagos Police Commissioner Ahlaji Abubakar Tsav was quoted by the TV
report as saying marine unit and police had been sent for rescue
operations.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the explosion is under investigation and no casualties
of the incident have been reported.
</P>
<P>
TV pictures show a big hole in the left front of the oil tanker,
which another witness said has been staying idle off the Apapa port
for more than one year.
</P>
<P>
The explosion produced thick smoke that can be seen a kilometer
away and affected nearby buildings.  
</P>
