<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 6 (Xinhua) -- China Trade Expo'97, the eighth of
its kind ever held in the New York City since 1990, opened at
Jacob K. Javits Convention Center here today.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 kinds of Chinese traditional and newly
developed products in 12 categories, including light industrial
products, textiles and garments, machinery, electronics, electric
appliance and equipment, native and animal by-products, cereal,
oil and foodstuffs, arts and crafts, metal and minerals,
metallurgical products, chemicals, petro-chemicals, are presented
to American traders.
</P>
