<HEADLINE> Majoli Takes French Open Women's Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Iva Majoli became the first Croatian
to take the French Open women's title with a straight-set victory
over top-ranked Martina Hingis of Switzerland on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Majoli, the ninth seed, gave top seed Hingis her first defeat
of the year by taking the finals 6-4, 6-2 in one hour 19 minutes.
</P>
<P>
This was the first grand slam title for the 19-year-old Majoli,
three years senior over teenager sensation Hingis.
</P>
<P>
Hingis, who became the youngest champion at the Australian Open
last January, was favoured to win for the first time on the Paris
clay.
</P>
<P>
But it was Majoli who depicted the game with powerful forehands
and fewer mistakes.
</P>
<P>
In the first set which last 39 minutes, Hingis had a sluggish
start and had to save six break points in the fifth game to hold
her service games.
</P>
<P>
Majoli broke Hingis in the seventh game with her powerful
forehands and held her service game to lead 5-3.
</P>
<P>
The second set saw Hingis distressed more and more. After
squandering three break points in the first game, Majoli broke
Hingis twice in the fifth and seventh games before sealing off the
competition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
