<HEADLINE> Pakistan, Russia Call for Intra-Afghan Dialogue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan and Russia have called
for an intra-Afghan dialogue to seek an "indigenous solution" of
the Afghan problem, according to official sources here today.
</P>
<P>
The call was here today when Pakistan Foreign Minister Gohar
Ayub met with visiting Russian Deputy Foreign Minister V.V.
Pauvaluk and discussed with him the evolving situation in
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The two sides share the view that an intra-Afghan dialogue
would lead to an indigenous solution of the problem resulting in
durable peace and stability, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
"It was also agreed to continue consultations on Afghanistan
which had proved useful in reaching a common understanding," they
said.
</P>
<P>
The Russian deputy foreign minister's visit was in continuation
of the process of consultations initiated by both countries to
coordinate their policies for facilitating a peaceful settlement
in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Pauvaluk reiterated Russia's support for peace and stability in
the region as a pre-requisite for the economic and political
development of all the countries in the region.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani Foreign Minister Gohar emphasized that collective
efforts should be made by the regional countries to bring the
conflict to an end and restoration of peace in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The two countries also expressed their commitment to the unity
and territorial integrity of Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Pauvaluk expressed his country's keen desire for regular
consultations with Pakistan on issues of mutual concern in the
bilateral and regional context, especially on the situation in
Afghanistan, the sources said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
