<HEADLINE> Thunderstorm Brings Flooding to Central China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- A thunderstorm that lasted for
more than ten hours caused severe flooding in central China's
Hunan Province, damaging more than 1,000 houses.
</P>
<P>
Heavy rains hit the cities of Changsha and Liuyang, and
Changsha County at around eight yesterday evening and continued
until eight this morning, when Changsha and Liuyang had
accumulated 219 mm and 297 mm of rainfall respectively.
</P>
<P>
Traffic and power supplies in some areas were cut, and in parts
of Changsha, the water rose to the third story of some buildings.
</P>
<P>
Hunan provincial government officials and those from local
governments spent a sleepless night directing the rescue and
flood-control efforts. Soldiers were also mobilized for the work.
</P>
<P>
Meteorologists say that another heavy rain is likely within two
days in Changsha.  
</P>
