<TEXT>
<P>
YANTAI, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Federico Chavez, a commercial
attache with the Mexican Trade Commission who is in charge of
market affairs in China, Hong Kong and Macao regions, says that
Mexico will increase trade cooperation with China in the future.
</P>
<P>
Chavez is heading a trade delegation to the Second Exposition
of Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) in Yantai, Shandong
Province, where he made the remarks to reporters today.
</P>
<P>
