materials, chemicals, textiles, and the electronic industries. It
will also expand its business in China in things like interior
decoration and carpet making,
</P>
<P>
Mexico's trade with 17 other members of APEC now makes up over
80 percent of the country's foreign trade, which is dominated by
the United States.
</P>
<P>
Mexico's trade with China accounts for less than one percent of
the country's total foreign trade, and stood at about 500 million
U.S. dollars in 1996, which he said was a small amount and that
they should increase trade cooperation with China.
</P>
<P>
Cerveza Sol International Ltd, one of Mexico's leading
enterprises, also participated in the exposition, which runs from
June 6 to 10.  
