<HEADLINE> 11 Cadets from New Delhi Drown in River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Eleven cadets from New Delhi,
capital of India, drowned in the Yamuna river Friday, an official
release said here today.
</P>
<P>
Out of 70 cadets who were swept away in the accident, 59 were
rescued. They were washed away by a sudden rush of water caused by
opening of barrage gates upstream of the river, the release said.
</P>
<P>
The cadets were attending a combined annual training camp from
May 28 which was to end Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Senior officers have rushed to the spot and relief and rescue
operations have been launched. Nine bodies have been recovered.
Aerial reconnaissance by army helicopters has been requisitioned
to locate the remaining bodies.
</P>
<P>
A high-level court of inquiry has been ordered to investigate
the circumstances leading to the tragedy.  
</P>
