<HEADLINE> Drug Traffickers Sentenced In South China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Three major drug traffickers
received the death sentence and were deprived of their political
rights for life in a final ruling by the Intermediate People's
Court of Shantou City, in Guangdong Province, today.
</P>
<P>
Zhuang Zhicheng was found guilty of trafficking in heroin and
selling 1.945 kg of heroin in Puning City from April to July of
1996, where he was arrested.
</P>
