<HEADLINE> Provisional Legislature Supports Transitional Budget </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Provisional Legislative
Council (PLC) of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR) today gave its support to the Transitional Budget for
1997-98.
</P>
<P>
At its 10th plenary meeting held here today, the PLC resumed
debate on a motion moved in May by the Chief Executive's Office of
the HKSAR to seek support of legislators for the Transitional
Budget for 1997-98.
</P>
<P>
The budget was worked out in line with the Basic Law -- the
constitutional document of Hong Kong after July 1, 1997, and the
consensus reached by the Sino-British Joint Liaison Group (JLG)
through 19 rounds of talks.
</P>
<P>
The British Hong Kong government looks after the first three
months covered by this financial budget, while the HKSAR
government will take care of the remaining nine months.
</P>
<P>
Many legislators rose to voice their favor of the budget,
which, they said, was conducive to the smooth transition of Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, they urged the future HKSAR government to
take into consideration such pressing issues as housing,
education, welfare for the elderly, industry, technology,
infrastructure and environment.
</P>
<P>
In a written report submitted today to the PLC, the Financial
Committee under the legislative body suggested that legislators'
views serve as useful reference points for compiling the budget
for the next financial year between 1998 and 1999.  
</P>
