<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HKSAR Provisional Legislature Adopts Three Bills on District Organizations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Urban Council (Amendment) Bill
1997, the Regional Council (Amendment) Bill 1997 and the District
Boards (Amendment) Bill 1997 were adopted here today by the
Provisional Legislative Council (PLC).
</P>
<P>
The three bills were tabled to the PLC for first and second
readings on May 17 by Michael Suen, secretary for policy
coordination of the Chief Executive's Office. The debate was then
adjourned and a bills committee composed of 18 PLC members was set
up to scrutinize the bills.
</P>
<P>
At today's full sitting, the three bills passed the third
reading with a great majority.
</P>
<P>
Under the bills, the Provisional Urban Council, the Provisional
Regional Council and 18 Provisional District Boards shall be
formed along with the founding of the HKSAR to operate in place of
the existing district organizations.
</P>
<P>
Considering that the tenure of office of the existing district
organizations end on June 30, 1997 and that members of the first
district organizations of the HKSAR can not be elected before July
1, 1997, it is necessary to set up the Provisional bodies to fill
a resultant vacuum.
</P>
<P>
Main contents of the three bills are as follows:
</P>
<P>
-- The Provisional Urban Council and the Provisional Regional
Council consist of not more than 50 members each, a 25-percent
increase over the existing councils, while each Provisional
District Board consists of not more than 40 members, also a
25-percent increase over the existing board.
</P>
<P>
-- The members of the bodies will be appointed by the Chief
Executive with their terms of office running not later than
December 31, 1999.
</P>
<P>
-- The members are required to swear that they will uphold the
Basic Law and that their allegiance is to the HKSAR before taking
up membership at the provisional district organizations.
</P>
<P>
-- The first meeting of the Provisional Urban Council, the
Provisional Regional Council and each of the Provisional District
Boards will be arranged before July 7, 1997, to elect a chairman
and a vice-chairman.
</P>
<P>
-- The rights, duties, obligations and liabilities of the
existing bodies will be assigned to the provisional bodies so as
to achieve a smooth transition.
</P>
<P>
The existing Urban Council and Regional Council in Hong Kong
are responsible for matter concerning public health, sanitation
and hygiene, the provision of recreational, sports and cultural
facilities and activities for Hong Kong residents. The District
Boards have a mainly advisory role in the management of district
affairs and provide a forum for public consultation and
participation at the district level.
</P>
<P>
Having passed the third reading at the provisional legislature,
the three bills have yet to go through a confirmation process
during the early hours of July 1 and gain assent of the Chief
Executive to become HKSAR law.
</P>
<P>
On May 10, the PLC had passed the Holidays (1997 and 1998)
Bill, the first draft legislation tabled to the legislature.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
