<HEADLINE> Syria: Israel Violates Human Rights in Occupied Land </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Syrian Minister of State for
Foreign Affairs Nasser Qaddour met here today with a delegation of
the UN Commission on investigating Israeli violations of human
rights in the occupied Arab territories.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the Syrian minister said his country was
keen on cooperating with the UN commission and was ready to offer
all possible facilities to help it fulfill the task of making
clear the human rights conditions in the Syrian Golan Heights as
well as other Arab territories occupied by Israel.
</P>
<P>
He said Syria "seeks to brief the international community on
the reality of Israeli practices that harm the land and the
people."
</P>
<P>
Qaddour pointed out that the commission should continue its
task till the end of its mandate when the Israeli occupation of
the Arab lands draws to a close.
</P>
<P>
The human rights conditions in the Golan Heights deteriorated
significantly and the international community should not only
condemn the Israeli policies and practices but also pressure
Israel to comply with relevant UN resolutions, Qaddour added.
</P>
<P>
The continuation of the Israeli practices runs counter to the
efforts that aim to establish a just and comprehensive peace in
the Middle East on the basis of the Madrid Peace Conference, he
emphasized.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian minister said Syrian-Israeli peace talks should be
resumed from where they were broke off and Israel should withdraw
to the June 4, 1967, border lines. 
</P>
