<HEADLINE> Legislative Council Commission Bill Passes Third Reading at PLC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 7 (Xinhua) -- A bill, which aims to facilitate
administrative support and services to the legislature of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) after July 1, won
unanimous support here today when receiving the third reading at a
plenary meeting of the Provisional Legislative Council (PLC).
</P>
<P>
The Legislative Council Commission (Amendment) Bill was tabled
by the Chief Executive's Office to the PLC for the first and
second readings at its previous plenary session.
</P>
<P>
The bill is to ensure the continued application of the existing
Legislative Council Commission Ordinance, which will continue to
be in force after the handover, and to make transitional
arrangements arising from the establishment of the PLC and its
supporting structure.
</P>
<P>
The bill provides for the adapted definitions of the
"Legislative Council," "Legislative Council Secretariat" and
"Legislative Council Commission" and makes changes to several
existing references -- such as substituting "Government" for
"Crown" -- so as to adapt to the post-handover situation.
</P>
<P>
Three other bills concerning district organizations of the
HKSAR were also adopted at today's meeting.
</P>
<P>
All the four bills, together with the Holidays (1997 and 1998)
Bill which had been passed earlier, have yet to go through a
confirmation process during the early hours of the establishment
of the HKSAR and to be signed by the HKSAR chief executive into
law.  
</P>
</TEXT>
