<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment Increases in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan attracted a total of
448.4 million U.S. dollars in foreign direct investment in the
first nine months of the current fiscal year (July 1996-March
1997).
</P>
<P>
During the period, portfolio investment in Pakistan amounted to
185.3 million dollars, according to sources from the Board of
Investment (BOI).
</P>
<P>
The sources said that since the new government led by Prime
Minister Nawaz Sharif came to power in February, foreign investors
have shown a renewed interest in Pakistan and are responding
positively to the economic reforms announced by the government.
</P>
<P>
According to figures provided by the BOI, the United Kingdom
remained at the top in terms of foreign direct investment with 183
million dollars. It was followed by the United States which
invested a total of 166.9 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
There have been visits by a number of high-level delegations
from South Korea and Japan, which plan to invest in Pakistan in a
big way, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Except for the 1995-96 fiscal year, the average foreign direct
investment during the last five years stood at around 335 million
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan attracted foreign direct investment worth 1.09 billion
dollars in the 1995-96 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
The BOI has forecast a major breakthrough in foreign direct
investment in the country during the current fiscal year.
</P>
</TEXT>
