mistakes and should analyze what all we have gained or lost. We
fought wars and spent so much on budget instead of concentrating
on the development of both the nations. It is high time we should
change our attitudes," he added.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistani people want good relations with India, Sharif
said. He called for a new beginning in ties between the two South
Asian nations.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the next round of foreign secretary-level talks
scheduled to be held here from June 19 to 22, Sharif made it clear
that the Kashmir issue should be discussed.
</P>
<P>
"It will not be in the interest of the two countries to talk
without keeping the Kashmir issue on the agenda," he said.
</P>
<P>
"I want to discuss all issues, but it would be better if we
talk about Kashmir," he added.
</P>
<P>
Sharif said he was hopeful that many problems between Pakistan
and India would be sorted out after the installation of a hotline
between the two prime ministers later this month.  
