<HEADLINE> Weekly Report on Kuala Lumpur Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Kuala Lumpur Stock
Exchange (KLSE) market closed the week stronger.
</P>
<P>
This week, the Composite Index gained 26.63 points to end at
1,104.83 from 1,078.20 last week, the Emas Index rose 3.86 points
to 313.74 and the Industrial Index increased 15.6 points to
2,098.63 while the second board Index fell 3.74 points to 569.45.
</P>
<P>
Security services company -- Safeguards Corporation was listed
on the second board on Friday when it opened at 4.80 ringgit
(about 1.92 U.S. dollars) for an impressive premium of 3.10
ringgit over its offer price of 1.70 ringgit, but closed at 4.68
ringgit after reaching day high of 5.05 ringgit with 3.520 million
shares traded.
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover decreased to 920.747 million shares
valued at 5.499 billion ringgit (about 2.1996 billion U.S.
dollars) from 968.720 million shares worth 5.860 billion ringgit
(about 2.344 billion U.S. dollars) last week.
</P>
<P>
Second board volume declined to 174.688 million shares worth
2.253 billion ringgit (about 901.2 million U.S. dollars) from
253.883 million shares valued at 3.284 billion ringgit (about
1.3136 billion U.S. dollars) last week.
</P>
<P>
Direct business deal however increased to 198.563 million
valued at 1.552 billion ringgit (about 620.8 million U.S. dollars)
from 134.260 million worth 1.361 billion ringgit (about 544.4
million U.S. dollars) last week.
</P>
<P>
The most active counter this week was MBf Capital which shed 15
sen to 5.20 ringgit on a turnover of 53.355 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Other counters in the top 10 which together contributed 28.96
percent of the total turnover, included up counters -- Wesmont
Industries, Samanda, Chase Perdana, and down counters -- Berjaya
Industrial, Renong, Anson Perdana, Sriwani, Sinora and YTL Power.
</P>
<P>
On sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 78.663
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products
209.080 million shares, construction 80.155 million shares,
trading/services 150.171 million shares, infrastructure 20.275
million shares, finance 135.227 million shares, hotels 13.813
million shares, properties 117.015 million shares, plantation
30.418 million shares, mining 1.933 million shares, trusts 1.404
million shares, closed end funds 2.331 million shares, loans
17.464 million shares, and TSR/warrants 45.141 million shares.
</P>
</TEXT>
