<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Kiswahili language as a subject
should be made compulsory for all Kenyan students pursuing degree
studies, Kenyan university teachers have urged.
</P>
<P>
Kiswahili is vital for regional cooperation, national unity,
democratic development and the development of technological
sciences, Moi University Vice-Chancellor Professor Justin Irina
was quoted by today's local press as saying.
</P>
