<HEADLINE> Chinese, Italian Trade Ministers Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- China and Italy have to promote the
volume of bilateral trade and investment, which are not
proportionate to the scale of the two economies, Chinese Minister
of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Wu Yi told her Italian
counterpart here today.
</P>
<P>
During talks with Augusto Fantozzi, Minister of Foreign Trade
from Italy, Wu said that the Chinese government places importance
on its relations with Italy in all aspects, including trade and
economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
She noted that in recent years, the increasing exchange of
visits between high-ranking officials of the two countries have had
a positive effect on the promotion of bilateral trade and economic
relations.
</P>
<P>
However, she pointed out that despite great progress has been
made in trade and investment between the two countries, the total
volume of investment and trade is yet to match the scale of the
two economies. She hopes that the two sides will work together to
fully develop the great potential of cooperation in these fields.
</P>
<P>
She said that China's reform, opening up and economic growth
have provided good opportunities for entrepreneurs from all over
the world. The Chinese government supports Italian businesses to
invest and conduct trade in China. Chinese enterprises will learn
from the experience of medium and small businesses in Italy, the
second biggest trade partner of China in the European Union (EU),
she said.
</P>
<P>
She expressed the hope that Italian businesses will further
improve their competitivity in China market and actively
participate in the development of central and western parts of the
country, the technology up-grading of state-owned enterprises and
construction of basic industries such as agriculture, energy,
telecommunications and transport.
</P>
<P>
Fantozzi said that the Italian government attaches great
importance to developing economic and trade relations with China,
which will become one of the centers of growth of the world
economy in the future.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Italian government will continue its efforts
to promote bilateral economic and trade cooperation to a new level.
</P>
<P>
This is not only in the interests of the enterprises and
economic growth of the two countries, but also a contribution to
the prosperity of the world as a whole, he said.
</P>
<P>
Wu also met with representatives from Italian business circles
after the talks.
</P>
<P>
Wu and Fantozzi attended the signing ceremony of an agreement
between the two countries on setting up a joint training course of
management for the Chinese side. The joint venture training course
is co-sponsored by the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation (MOFTEC) of China and Bordiga Galgano and Associates
of Italy.  
</P>
