the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Chinese individuals has always been the key sources for
commercial banks to lure deposits.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics from the People's Bank of China, the central
bank, show that China's personal savings rocketed to 4,155 billion
yuan (500 billion dollars) by the end of May.
</P>
<P>
The country's personal bank savings will top 4,700 billion yuan
(566 billion dollars) by the end of this year, the paper quoted Xu
Hongyuan, an expert of the State Planning Commission Information
Center, as estimating.  
