<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepal Granted Duty-Free Treatment by U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Nepal will for the first time get
duty-free treatment from the United States for some specified
products, press reports here said today.
</P>
<P>
In addition to Nepal, 37 other least developed countries,
including Bangladesh, Bhutan, Yemen and Cambodia, will enjoy the
additional trade benefits under the U.S. Generalized Systems of
Preferences (GSP) program.
</P>
<P>
The countries can enjoy the new benefits immediately except
Cambodia, where the GSP treatment will not come into force until
July.
</P>
<P>
The GSP program provides duty-free treatment for specified
products from more than 140 designated beneficiary countries and
regions.
</P>
<P>
The United States is the largest market for Nepal's ready-made
garment exports, worth about 20 million U.S. dollars every year.
</P>
</TEXT>
