<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian King Tuanku Ja'afar
today honored the country's six army corps by presenting them with
royal colors.
</P>
<P>
"The royal honors bestowed upon them means that the corps must
continue to uphold and enhance their excellent performance," the
King said when presenting royal colors to the corps before "a
trooping of the color" parade at Independence Stadium here to mark
his 75th birthday today.
</P>
