<HEADLINE> Domestic Stock Market Falls After PBOC Ban </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- China stock market plunged in
reaction to the central bank's banning of commercial banks from
stock trading, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
The index of the Shanghai Stock Exchange dropped 84.8 points to
end at 1275.3 Friday, and the figure at the Shenzhen Stock
Exchange lost 288.23 points, to close at 4847.
</P>
<P>
There will be no big price fall in stocks bought for long-term
investors, says stock-trading brokers.
</P>
<P>
Investors understood the People's Bank of China's decree was in
line with the chain of measures by the government to control
speculation in the stock market, they says.
</P>
<P>
China's two stock market witnesses a sharp increase in trading
volume-both hitting 13 billion yuan(1.6 US dollars), indicating
that illicit money was fleeing the market after the PBOC on
Thursday ordered banks to clear their positions within ten days.
</P>
