<HEADLINE> Romanian Parliament Vetos No-confidence Motion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The two chambers of Romanian
parliament, the Senate and the Chamber of Deputies, on Friday
vetoed a no-confidence motion raised by opposition parliament
members against the government.
</P>
<P>
During the parliamentary meeting, up to 277 members were
against the motion with 156 votes for it.
</P>
<P>
Some 140 opposition deputies, who tabled the motion, attributed
the depressed economy in Romania in the past half years as well as
the drop of people's living standard to the economic reform
measures adopted by Prime Minister Victor Ciorbea's government.
</P>
<P>
Ciorbea, who came to power in November 1996, said that the
current hard situation is a left-over by previous government
instead of his fault. He added his cabinet has adopted some
mandates to improve people's living standard. 
</P>
