<HEADLINE> Highlights of Major Beijing-Based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major
Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
All the newspapers reported on the frontpage that the correct
use of the Chinese national flag and the regional flag of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) have been defined in
regulations passed by the 58th executive meeting of the State
Council, held in Beijing on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
All the newspapers also reported on the frontpage Chinese
President Jiang Zemin said here yesterday that China and Italy
should make concerted efforts to actively push forward the
development of bilateral friendly and cooperative relations for
the 21st century. Jiang made the remark here yesterday morning
when meeting with visiting Italian Prime Minister Romano Prodi.
</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
--President Jiang Zemin, meeting yesterday with delegates to the
Communist Party of China (CPC) Congress of Armed Police, urged
them to reinforce the building of the Party in the Armed Police
and to improve its fighting capability.
</P>
<P>
--President Jiang Zemin called yesterday for an intensified
military training and an accelerated modernization of both
equipment and technology while meeting with delegates to a meeting
of the Second Artillery Force of the People's Liberation Army.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also urged delegates to adhere to Deng Xiaoping's theory of
building socialism with Chinese characteristics and his theory of
building the army in the new period.
</P>
<P>
--Farmers of flood-hit Pingshan County, Hebei Province, have
now been busy turning more wasteland into arable farmland.
</P>
<P>
Pingshan, together with Jingxing and Zanhuang counties, were
hit by serious floods last August and a lot of the arable land were
washed away.
</P>
<P>
 "China Youth News"
</P>
<P>
Four citizens of Myanmar who were found guilty of drug
trafficking in China were sentenced to death and executed in
Yunnan Province yesterday, according to sources of the Superme
People's Court.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
The Industrial and Commercial Bank of China (ICBC), the
country's leading commercial bank, yesterday announced its
outstanding deposits had hit 2,055 billion yuan by May 31.
</P>
<P>
"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- China pledged to plunge deeper into the Asia-Pacific trade
network at the on-going second APEC International Trade Fair held
in Yantai, a coastal city of east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
--The recruitment of civil servants through open examinations,
introduced three years ago, has paid off in improving the
efficiency and quality of China's government offices, an official
from the Ministry of Personnel said. 
