<HEADLINE> Anti-Drug Show Goes on Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- A nation-wide tour to educate young
people about the dangers of narcotics will be started from
Guangzhou, capital of south China's Guangdong Province, in
mid-June, today's "China Daily" reported.
</P>
<P>
The show, the first of its kind in China, will focus on the
harmful effects of drugs and present results of a study on drug
problems by China Juvenile Delinquency Research Institute (CJDRI).
</P>
<P>
After being shown in Guangzhou for a month, the exhibit, which
employs some 300 photographs to show ill effects of using
narcotics, will move to other cities of south, southwest, and
northwest China through the first half of 1998.
</P>
<P>
By 1995, China counted 520,000 drug addicts, most them young
people. In Yunnan Province, for instance, 60 percent of the drug
abusers are under 25 years of age. 
</P>
</TEXT>
