<HEADLINE> Russia Welcomes Extension of UN's Oil For Food Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Russia on Friday welcomed the U.N.
Security Council's decision to prolong its "Oil for Food" program
for Iraq for another six months.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Foreign Ministry said that the extension of
U.N. resolution 986 will ease the current food shortage in Iraq,
which is still very serious in the country, Itar-Tass news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The resolution, which was adopted by the United Nations in
April 1995 to allow Iraq to export 2 billion U.S. dollars of oil
to buy food and medicine, was prolonged by the Security Council on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Russia said it is of great humanitarian and political
significance to carry out resolution 986, which will improve
Iraq's relations with other countries in the world.
</P>
<P>
Russia also hoped to ease and eventually lift all sanctions
against Iraq through the implementation of the U.N. decision.
</P>
