<HEADLINE> Money Laundering by Political Parties Probed in Ecuador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The Ecuadoran Congress opened an
investigation into the bank accounts of several political parties
and some companies suspected of being involved in laundering of
drug traffic money.
</P>
<P>
The investigation were made at the level of the whole Andean
region, in coordination with the police of each country, officials
from the Interpol central bureau were quoted as saying today.
</P>
<P>
They said police reports on the bleaching of money of the
Ecuadoran political parties will be delivered and published
through the Congressional Commission on Drug Trafficking.
</P>
<P>
The Commission has confidential evidences about money
laundering, used especially in electoral campaigns, in which large
amounts of resources were used openly for the promotion of
candidates.
</P>
<P>
The National Congress will request from the Superintendency of
Companies a detailed registry of national and foreign anonymous
companies that were established in Ecuador between August 1992 and
December 1996.
</P>
<P>
The inquest will require a report on the origin of the
financial resources, the nationality of the partners or
shareholders and the geographical location of the firms under the
control of the Superintendence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
