<HEADLINE> Italian FM Urges Closer Cooperation With France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto Dini
today congratulated his French counterpart Hubert Vedrine on his
new appointment and expressed his hope for closer cooperation in
accelerating European integration.
</P>
<P>
While wishing Vedrine success in his mandate, Dini said Italy
and France, sharing broad common interests, particularly in
deepening European integration and enlarging the European Union
(EU), could pursue more agreements during Vedrine's term.
</P>
<P>
"I refer especially to the process of extending European
integration, prior to the expansion of the union, which is at the
center of our common efforts to guarantee economic and social
development and heightened security for all member states," he
said in a letter.
</P>
<P>
Describing Italian-French cooperation as "decisive" in
expanding NATO and in the mechanism of the Group of Seven
industrialized nations, Dini said the two countries should work
together to ensure the stability in the Balkans and the
Mediterranean.
</P>
<P>
Hailing the "excellent understanding" between the two countries
in the U.N.-authorized Multinational Protection Force sent to
Albania, Dini said he is looking forward to better coordination.
