<HEADLINE> Central China Province Hits Record High In Summer Grain Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, June 7 (Xinhua)-- Henan Province in central China is
expected to hit a record high in its summer grain production this
year, which is estimated at some 23.68 billion kg, a year-on-year
increase of 15.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Farmers attribute the good harvest to more effective
application of agro-sciences and favorable weather conditions. The
provincial agriculture department has promoted the use of deep
ploughing and other practical technologies.
</P>
<P>
Early this year, Henan began to carry out a farmland
improvement project and a seed project, encourage farmers to
collect more organic manures, and use high-yielding strains of
wheat, which have been sown to more than 95 percent of the total
farmland this year.
</P>
<P>
Local governments increased their efforts to support farmers
both in policy and funds, as the State raised the purchasing
price for grains to encourage farmers to expand grain production.
</P>
</TEXT>
