<HEADLINE> Chinese Defense Minister Meets Ukrainian Parliament Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi Haotian
today met Ukrainian parliament Speaker Alexander Moroz.
</P>
<P>
Moroz said Chi's visit is an important step in the relations
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Chi's visit proves again that China and Ukraine enjoy sound
relations, Moroz said, adding that his visit would broaden
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also vice-chairman of China's Central Military Commission,
said, "It's my long-time wish to visit Ukraine."
</P>
<P>
He said China supports Ukraine's foreign policy of
independence, neutrality and nonalignment and respects Ukraine's
independence, sovereignty and territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
Chi also met his Ukrainian counterpart, Alexander Kuzmuk, today.
</P>
<P>
During his talks with Kuzmuk, Chi called for stronger military
links between the two countries. He hoped that bilateral
cooperation in military equipment and technology will be developed
alongside with the overall bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Chi is the highest-ranking Chinese military official who has
visited Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
He is on his second leg of a four-nation tour in the former
Soviet republics. He arrived in Kiev today after a visit to
Belarus.
</P>
<P>
After his five-day stay in Ukraine, he will go on to visit
Kazakhstan and Kyrgyzstan. 
