<HEADLINE> Venezuela Sues Greek Ship for Environmental Damage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The owners of a Greek ship that
leaked oil in Lake Maracaibo a few weeks ago were sued in a
Venezuelan court for an environmental damage of 5 billion bolivars
(some 10.5 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
A preventive embargo has been decreed to prevent the ship from
leaving Venezuela, Attorney General of the Republic Juan
Nepomuceno Garrido said today.
</P>
<P>
He said the authorities are assessing the damage caused to the
lake, estimated at 5 billion bolivars, which is equivalent to the
sum of deposits of the owners of the shipping company in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The "Nissos Amorgos" Greek ship ran aground several weeks ago
in the Maracaibo Lake navigation channel and leaked a large
quantity of oil it carried. 
</P>
