<HEADLINE> Old-Age Insurance Developing Fast in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 7 (Xinhua) -- This leading industrial city of
China has made remarkable progress in developing old-age
insurance, which so far covered 6.15 million workers and staff,
representing 95 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is a city with increasing number of aged people, with
those above 60 years old accounting for 17 percent of the total
population, local sources said.
</P>
<P>
The city started old-age insurance reform in 1992 and a
comprehensive insurance system covering the whole society has
initially taken shape.
</P>
<P>
However, in addition to the practice of the basic old-age
insurance system which aims to guarantee the basic living of those
involved, the city launched a complementary old-age insurance
which is designed to maintain living standards for the aged people
amid inflation.
</P>
<P>
To date, some 150,000 workers and staff from 100 Shanghai-based
enterprises have participated in the newly-launched drive of
complementary old-age insurance, with the old-age insurance fund
amounting to 200 million yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
