<HEADLINE> Iranian Deputy FM Met Anti-Taliban Faction Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Deputy Foreign Minister
Alauddim Brajourdi yesterday held talks with leaders of factions
opposing Afghan Islamic Taliban militia in northern Afghanistan,
sources said.
</P>
<P>
Brajourdi met with General Abdul Malik in Mazar-e-Sharif,
capital city of northwestern Balkh province, the Afghan sources in
Pakistan said.
</P>
<P>
Malik, whose revolt forced northern warlord Rashid Dostum to
flee the country, turned his back on the Taliban late last month
only four days after their allied forces entered Mazar-e-Sharif.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, Brajourdi told the press that the on-going
Afghan crisis could not be solved through military solution while
urging all Afghan warring parties to reach a consensus to form a
broad-based government, said the sources in Peshawar, Pakistan's
northwestern major city.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that Brajourdi yesterday also held talks with
ousted Afghan president Burhanuddin Rabbani in Feyzabad, capital
of Badakhshan province.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Taliban fighters were engaged in fierce fighting
with forces loyal to Malik and former military chief Ahmad Masood
in Samagan and Badakhshan provinces respectively, they said.
</P>
</TEXT>
