<HEADLINE> Shandong To Set Up Container Through Transport Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, June 7 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province plans
to set up an international container through transport network with
the Qingdao Harbor at the core.
</P>
<P>
Container facilities will be built in a dozen cities in
Shandong including the provincial capital Jinan and Weifang, Zibo,
Tai'an and Jining cities.
</P>
<P>
The network, which will link with neighboring provinces, is
scheduled to increasing the province's transferring of
international containers to as much as one million TEUs, from the
present 500,000 TEUs.
</P>
<P>
The total investment for the project is 1.02 billion yuan
including 50.7 million US dollars in foreign exchange. The
province plans to build the project with foreign participation in
the forms of investment or cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Once completed, the project is expected to bring in over 400
million yuan as gross income and 135 million yuan in profits each
year, according to local officials. 
