<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader Visits Siemens Management Training Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FELDAFING, Germany, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese leader Li
Ruihuan visited here this afternoon the international management
training center of the German electronics and engineering group
Siemens AG.
</P>
<P>
Li, chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), is on a seven-day
official goodwill visit to Germany which began Thursday in Munich,
capital of the southern German state of Bavaria.
</P>
<P>
He arrived at Feldafing, a small lake-side resort some 40
kilometers south of Munich after a visit to the headquarters of
the Daimler-Benz Aerospace AG Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
Matthias Bellmann, head of the Siemens training center, made a
detailed introduction to the Chinese leader on how Siemens trains
its business managers against the backdrop of globalization. He
then showed Li around the center which features many modern
training facilities.
</P>
<P>
Siemens, which celebrates this year the 150th anniversary of
its founding, has been doing business with China for over 100
years.
</P>
<P>
According Siemens statistics, the company now has employees of
over 10,000 in China and its annual sales in the country have
reached one billion U.S. dollars. So far Siemens has established
35 joint ventures and two solely-funded enterprises in China. It
is also expected to open a management training center in Beijing
at the end of September. 
</P>
</TEXT>
